          <head/>
          <msContents>
            <summary>A modern short treatise on decimal fractions written in 1855 CE by Bir Khurdār
              Jīlā, who dedicated it to Major George William Hamilton, superintendent of the Ṣūba of
              Multān.</summary>

            <msItem xml:id="MS-ARABIC-00430-item1">
              <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="">al-Kusūr al-ʿashārīyah</title>
              <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt">الكسور الاعشارية</title>
              <title xml:lang="en" type="alt">Decimal fractions</title>
              <author><persName>Barkhurdār Jīlā</persName> (<persName>برخوردار بن نور محمد
                  جيلا</persName>)</author>

              <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
              <note><p>Some explanatory notes in the margins.</p>
                <p>From the colophon on <locus from="5b">folio 5b</locus> it appears that manuscript
                  is an autograph.</p></note>
              <colophon>حرره الفقير برحوردار بن نور محمد جيلا ... بتاريخ ١٦ رجب سنة ١٢٧١ هجرة سنة
                ١٨٥٥ عيسوية</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>

